{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"decahedral-flaming-agouti","description":"## Why\nToday rebar has TWO session resolvers with DIFFERENT precedence chains:\n`session_log._resolve_session_fp` (`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID -> REBAR_SESSION_ID ->\nSESSION_ID -> None`) and `transition_close._resolve_session` (`REBAR_SESSION_ID ->\nSESSION_ID -> git HEAD -> \"unknown\"`). The latter OMITS `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID`, so in a\nreal Claude Code session the FORCE_CLOSE audit comment falls through to git HEAD — a value\nthat changes every commit and is not a session id. This is a latent bug and the two must\nconverge before anything else in the epic builds on session resolution.\n\n## What\nIntroduce one shared `resolve_session_id()` helper implementing the ordered, extensible\nvar list (explicit rebar var first, native harness vars by popularity, ambient last):\n`REBAR_SESSION_ID -> CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID -> OPENCODE_SESSION_ID -> CODEX_THREAD_ID ->\nSESSION_ID -> None`. The list is a single data-driven array so new harness vars are a\none-line add. Refactor both existing call sites onto it. The FORCE_CLOSE call site keeps\nits cosmetic HEAD/\"unknown\" fallback locally, but the shared resolver returns None on\nabsence.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the shared helper, the ordered list, refactoring the two existing resolvers, unit\n  tests for the precedence chain, docs for the env-var contract.\n- OUT: recording the id on claims (S2); reducer/read/hook work (later stories).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] New `resolve_session_id()` returns the first set var in the ordered list, else None.\n- [ ] `session_log` and `transition_close` both call the shared helper (no duplicate chains).\n- [ ] FORCE_CLOSE audit now captures `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` when present (bug fixed).\n- [ ] Never returns git HEAD as the session id.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: each var precedence, empty-string handling, all-absent -> None.\n- [ ] `docs/config.md` (or event-schema) documents the ordered contract.\n","id":"6014-0863-2e36-41b3","parent_id":"38ec-5f12-fdf5-4340","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Unify session-id resolution into one shared, ordered resolver (+ fix FORCE_CLOSE Claude Code session bug)"},"env_id":"724d9d0c-bc4c-4cc4-b96b-1a19356102e2","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783481172504216193,"uuid":"adff5631-e7db-4600-b14b-54c901abd2ea"}